<TITLE> Bhuiyan says Jan 11 changeover saved nation from civil war </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 15 (bdnews24.com)  BNP's reformist leader Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan Monday said the January 11 changeover had saved the country from further bloody violence. "The long-drawn political conflict led to the imposition of the state of emergency. There was a growing fear of the country plunging into a civil war. The state of emergency saved us from the worst," Bhuiyan said when he made an Eid visit to his constituency of Narsinghdi. He repeated the need for reforms to the BNP and said: "The country will never return to the days before the Jan 11 changeover. We have to reform the party to make it acceptable to people." Besides exchanging greetings with local people, he held a meeting with political leaders and workers. bd
